As far as the part about parents knowing their own child best - I think you have to draw a line between different types of knowledge. Parents spend much more time around their child than doctors. They know, far better than the doctor can, what the child's symptoms are, how normal or abnormal their behavior is, what the child has done and been exposed to before becoming sick, etc. But the doctor is far better equipped than the parent is to put these facts together and determine what is wrong and how to treat it. The parents supply concrete facts, the doctors supply connections and advice.
